AGI -&nbsp;New intervention of the Privacy Authority against the phenomenon of wild telemarketing. The Authority has ordered Wind Tre spa to pay a penalty of 347.520 euros for unlawful processing of personal data for promotional purposes > and for the failure to adopt technical and organizational measures able to guarantee the privacy of customers within the reserved areas of the site of Wind Tre. The provision of the Guarantor arrives at the end of an investigation initiated following several notices of users who complained about the receipt of undesirable promotional calls and the complaint of a customer who reported that, in their reserved area, the personal data of another customer.
The Authority, also as a result of inspection activities, found, in particular, that Wind Tre for telemarketing activities had benefited from some commercial partners using illicitly collected contact lists. > In fact, in many cases, the lists were formed by extra subjects EU without adequate guarantees, consents were not properly demonstrated and retention times too extended or even not indicated.
The Garante finally ascertained the inadequacy of the technical-organizational measures relating to the registration system to the reserved area of the customers and the failure to notify the Authority of the violation of the personal data of the customer. In determining the amount of the penalty, the Guarantor took into account the full collaboration offered by the company, > of the data categories concerned by the violations (common data) and of the advanced level of technical-organizational and security implementation measures that the company had begun to change before the investigation in view of the accession to the Code of Conduct on telemarketing and teleselling.&nbsp;

