AGI - The Regional Council of Lazio chaired by Francesco Rocca, on a proposal from the Councillor for Tourism Elena Palazzo, approved, through deliberation, to adopt and submit to the examination of the Regional Council the proposal of Deliberazione Consiliare concerning the "Approval of the three-year tourist plan 2025-2027 of the Lazio Region".
&nbsp;
"An important step, necessary to start the phase of confrontation in the Regional Council - declares the Councillor for Tourism, Environment and Sport Elena Palazzo - is a decisive moment that entrusts to the general discussion the work we have done until today, carried out with the same principle, that is to say that of sharing. In fact, in recent months I felt it appropriate to start listening with operators, associations of category, local administrators and residents, personally crossing the province by province. The work of processing has given rise to a text that transposes many of the indications collected and inserts them into our political vision."
&nbsp;
The Triennial Plan of Tourism, whose contents were anticipated last February 5 in Rome, on the occasion of the First Tourism Forum, outlines the actions to be put in place for a structural relaunch of this sector. It aims to make Lazio a diversified and accessible tourist destination, enhancing not only Rome but all the regional territory >. The strategy focuses on innovation, through App and artificial intelligence, and synergies between the various actors to improve the competitiveness of the tourism sector. Among the objectives is the creation of an internationally recognized "Brand Lazio". The concept of 'turisms' replaces the traditional vision of tourism, including new destinations and products, different types and targets of visitors for a more competitive approach and in line with current market needs.
&nbsp;
"We want to allow tourists to have a wide range of services available to meet the specific needs, even in compliance with the inclusivity - explains the city council member Palazzo - for this we expect to continue with our promotional campaign There is all a Lazio around" "I wish good work to the President of the Tourism Commission Luciano Crea who will have to coordinate the work of the Chamber. Tourism is one of the leading sectors of the economy in Lazio. I'm sure - the Councillor concludes - that we will soon come to outline our definitive Triennial Plan, thus giving us a precious tool that will allow us to better value such a decisive asset". &nbsp;

